Note that the first attempt to recover the 3D displacement-field point defect function was made in
 
  19
  using the so-called simultaneous algebraic reconstruction technique (SART) algorithm (
 cf.
 
  13
 ). Unfortunately, the SART solutions turn out to converge only for a limited number of voxels (no more than 5 × 5 × 5 = 125 voxels) near around a point defect in a crystal.
